We use two nested loops to iterate through the bulbs and their corresponding buttons. The outer loop represents the number of button presses, and the inner loop represents the bulbs being flipped. We use bitwise XOR operation to toggle the bulbs based on the button pressed. The time complexity is O(n) because we iterate through all bulbs once, regardless of the number of presses. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a single variable to store the bulb status. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only performs bitwise operations and does not require any significant energy consumption.

